Bg7 14. Qe2 Nf5 15. Ne5 $1 {White's position is much better anyway, but now is
a good moment to increase the advantage.} Nxe5 (15... Bb7 16. Ng5 $16) 16. fxe5
Rb8 17. Bg5 Qc7 18. Nf6+ Kh8 19. Rae1 Bb7 20. g4 Ne7 21. Bxb7 Qxb7 22. Rf3 (22.
Qf2 $5 $18 {[%cal Gf2h4] followed by Qh4.}) 22... Ng8 23. Ref1 h6 24. Rh3 {
White is attacking with simple, but very effective, moves.} Rf7 25. Qd2 Nxf6
26. exf6 Kg8 27. Bf4 (27. Rhf3 $1 hxg5 28. Qxg5 Rbf8 29. Qxg6 $18) 27... e5 28.
Bxe5 Re8 29. Qf4 $16 {Nakamura,H (2775)-Kryvoruchko,Y (2707) Dubai (rapid)
2014 (1-0, 39)} *

