1968 (½-½, 53)} 20. Qf1 $5 {[%cal Gg2h3] Threatening Bh3.} Qxa2 21. Nb5 Ba6
22. Ra1 Bxb5 23. Qxb5 Qe6 24. Rxa7 Nc6 25. Raa1 $14 {Black's control on e5
makes his position solid, but his weakened queenside is a source of worries.})
17. fxe5 Bxe5 18. Bf4 ({As so many other times, the best move consists of
