125,85,117,79,169,217,239,210,239,279,269,212,286,261,261,261,275,269,286,291,
520,501]} 1. f4 e5 2. fxe5 d6 3. exd6 Bxd6 4. Nf3 g5 $5 {A very brutal move,
threatening ...g5-g4 followed by ...Qh4+.} 5. g3 g4 6. Nh4 Ne7 {I must confess
that during the aforementioned game this (actually logical) move took me by
complete surprise. Black plans ...Ng6, most likely resulting into the opening
