game) are:} 7. e4 Ng6 8. Nf5 Bxf5 9. exf5 {It seems to me that Black has
adequate compensation after} Qe7+ 10. Qe2 Ne5 11. Bg2 Nbc6 12. c3 O-O-O) (7. d4
{is stronger than 7.e4 but not entirely clear either:} Ng6 8. Nxg6 hxg6 9. Qd3
