corr 1974 (1-0, 23)}) (9... d4 $146 10. Nd5 Be6 11. c4 dxc3 12. Qa4+ $1 Qd7 13.
Qxd7+ Kxd7 14. Nxc3 {Black's king is exposed and the queenside is in big
danger. Here is a beautiful (in its logic and fluency) variation:} Rb8 15. Bf4
Bxf4 16. Rxf4 Ne7 17. Ra4 a6 18. Ne4 Rhc8 19. Rc1 $16) 10. e4 d4 (10... dxe4
11. Nxe4 O-O 12. c3 $16 {With pressure on both wings, Galchenko, M (1878)
