-88,25,29,17,13]} 1. f4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. g3 g6 4. Bg2 Bg7 5. O-O {In this line
we will examine several alternatives to 6...c5.} O-O ({Since at a later stage .
..b7-b5 allows the central break, it is worth mentioning} 5... b5 {before
White has managed to play d2-d3. The best reaction is to switch to play on
dark squares, because precisely those were weakened on the last move.} 6. c3
Bb7 7. a4 a6 8. axb5 axb5 9. Rxa8 Bxa8 {Sagit,R (2411)-Dziuba,M (2573)
Vasteras 2017 (½-½, 55)} 10. Ne5 O-O 11. d4 Nbd7 12. Qd3 c6 13. Nd2 Qc7 14.
Nb3 $14) 6. d3 Nc6 {To tell the truth, this is some sort of game spoiler, as
it more or less forces White to switch to boring play. Black's main idea is
preparing ... e7-e5 without allowing the desirable Nc3 under favourable
circumstances (due to ...d5-d4). The main drawback of the last move is that it
blocks the own c-pawn.} (6... Nbd7 {is by far more passive.} 7. Nc3 Re8 8. e4
dxe4 9. dxe4 e5 $2 10. fxe5 Ng4 11. Bg5 $16) (6... b5 {is simplest met with} 7.
