{Do you remember the best plan for White in this position?} 7. Qe1 $1 {This is
my favourite manoeuvre in a similar line with reversed colours and in the main
system examined below. White slowly prepares e2-e4.} Bb7 {When playing and
analyzing this position I got the distinct feeling that White's extra tempo
puts him into some sort of psychological Zugzwang! After many hesitations, I
choose the next move as the most constructive:} 8. a4 $1 Nbd7 {The most
straightforward move, preparing ...e7-e5. Its drawback is allowing the next,
highly desirable, White move.} 9. Nc3 $1 {Now that ...d5-d4 is not possible,
White has no reasons to refrain from this move, already threatening e2-e4.} *

